{{coord|51.50455|-0.37669|display=title|region:GB_scale:2000}}
'''Amar Radio''' is a community [[radio]] channel, aimed at the Asian community. Based in [[Southall]], [[London]], it was launched on 27 June 2002 as Akash Radio.<ref>{{cite news |first=Lakh |last=Baddhan |publisher=Media 247 UK Limited |work=Biz Asia UK |title=Akash Radio celebrates 7th year with newspaper |url=http://www.media247.co.uk/bizasia/akash-radio-celebrates-7th-year-with-newspaper |date=3 June 2009 |accessdate=14 January 2013}}</ref>

During May 2010, Akash Radio had a change of management with the name, imaging and content all undergoing a refresh. Akash Radio became known as Amar Radio.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://media247.co.uk/bizasia/newsarchive/2010/05/akash_radio_bec.php|title=Akash Radio becomes Amar Radio|publisher=Biz Asia|date=31 May 2010|access-date=27 July 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100926111208/http://media247.co.uk/bizasia/newsarchive/2010/05/akash_radio_bec.php|archive-date=26 September 2010|dead-url=yes|df=dmy-all}}</ref> In December 2010, Jaswant Singh, the President of [[Southall]]'s Miri Piri Gurdwara bought Amar Radio with plans to give the station an overhaul.<ref>{{cite news |first=Raj |last=Baddhan |publisher=Media 247 UK Limited |work=Biz Asia UK |title=Amar Radio has change of management – again! |url=http://www.media247.co.uk/bizasia/amar-radio-has-change-of-management-again |date=6 December 2010 |accessdate=14 January 2013}}</ref>

Amar Radio is accessible via its [[website]] worldwide and features popular discussion, cultural, and [[Bhangra (music)|bhangra]] shows. Amar Radio was available across the United Kingdom and Ireland from [[Sky (UK & Ireland)|Sky Digital]] until 15 August 2011.<ref>{{cite news |first=Raj |last=Baddhan |publisher=Media 247 UK Limited |work=Biz Asia UK |title=New numbers for Asian channels on Sky Digital |url=http://www.media247.co.uk/bizasia/new-numbers-for-asian-channels-on-sky-digital |date=13 October 2005 |accessdate=14 January 2013}}</ref>

The station has won two Asian award nominations for best radio station,{{Citation needed|date=October 2008}} and is a sponsor of shows and [[mela]]s within the local community.

