'''American International School of Libreville''' ('''AISL''') is an American [[international school]] in [[Libreville]], [[Gabon]]. The [[Embassy of the United States, Libreville|U.S. Embassy in Gabon]] sponsors the school. It serves grades pre-kindergarten through grade 12,<ref>"[https://www.state.gov/m/a/os/219577.htm Gabon, Libreville: American International School of Libreville]." [[U.S. Department of State]]. Retrieved April 26, 2015.</ref> and was founded in 1975 at the request of the [[U.S. Ambassador to Gabon]]. The school's student body for the year 2015–2016 was 26. As of 2015, there were no eleventh and twelfth graders at the school.<ref>"[http://www.aislgabon.info/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=111&Itemid=466 About] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150811051137/http://aislgabon.info/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=111&Itemid=466 |date=2015-08-11 }}." American International School of Libreville. Retrieved April 26, 2015.</ref>

