'''Digital Kosovo''' is a digital advocacy platform, a component of the Digital Diplomacy Strategy of the  [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Kosovo)]] and implemented by the Kosovan entrepreneur [[Kushtrim Xhakli]] and IPKO Foundation, with support of the [[British Council]] and [[Norwegian Embassy]]. The initiative is focused on enabling Kosovo citizens to act as digital diplomats, take part in online advocacy and help integrate Kosovo into the digital landscape.<ref>{{cite news |title=Kosovo's Digital Diplomats |url=https://foreignpolicy.com/articles/2013/12/06/kosovo_s_digital_diplomats |newspaper=Foreign Policy Magazine |date=6 December 2013 |accessdate=6 December 2013}}</ref>

The platform launched on 2 September 2013 with the sole aim of supporting Kosovo's integration into the digital world, and ever since it has mobilised a community of over 1,200 active users who are engaged in hundreds of digital diplomacy actions by sending requests to different institutions.<ref>{{cite news |title=Digital Kosovo - Successfully Integrating Kosovo Into the Digital World |url=http://ipkofoundation.org/activities/digital-kosovo-successfully-integrating-kosovo-into-the-digital-world |newspaper=IPKO Foundation |date=10 December 2013 |accessdate=10 December 2013}}</ref> As of February 2014, Digital Kosovo has successfully integrated Kosovo on popular platforms like [[Facebook]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Kosovo Attains Status (on Facebook) It Has Sought for Years: Nation|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/12/13/world/europe/kosovo-seeking-recognition-follows-the-crowd-to-facebook-social-media.html|publisher=The New York Times|accessdate=3 March 2013}}</ref> [[Google]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Kosovo displayed as location on Google|url=http://www.digitalkosovo.org/kosovo-location-google/|work=Digital Kosovo|publisher=Digital Kosovo|accessdate=27 February 2014}}</ref>  [[Dropbox (service)|Dropbox]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Kosovo now on Dropbox|url=http://www.digitalkosovo.org/kosovo-now-on-dropbox/|work=Digital Kosovo|accessdate=27 February 2014}}</ref> [[Oracle Corporation|Oracle]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Create Your Oracle Account |url=https://myprofile.oracle.com/EndUser/faces/profile/createUser.jspx |work=Oracle |publisher=Oracle |accessdate=27 February 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140715141541/https://myprofile.oracle.com/EndUser/faces/profile/createUser.jspx |archivedate=15 July 2014 |df=dmy }}</ref> [[World Wide Web Consortium]].<ref>{{cite web|title=This week at W3C: TimBL on pervasive surveillance, #TPAC2013, Spec: CSS Transitions Draft, etc.|url=http://www.w3.org/blog/2013/11/this-week-at-w3c-timbl-on-pervasive-surveillance-tpac2013-spec-css-transitions-draft-etc/|work=World Wide Web Consortium|publisher=World Wide Web Consortium|accessdate=27 February 2014}}</ref>

==Awards==
On 28 December 2013, Digital Kosovo initiative won Digital Engagement of the year on the Digital Diplomacy Review published by Yenidiplomasi.com, a platform for advocacy, research, training, consulting and publication of digital diplomacy issues.<ref>{{cite web|title=Digital Engagement of the Year|url=http://digjitale.com/2013/12/digital-engagement-year-goes-digital-kosovo/|work=The Digital Diplomacy Review|publisher=Yenidiplomasi.com|accessdate=27 February 2014}}</ref>

