'''"I Love You"''' is a song composed by [[Brandon Stone (composer)|Brandon Stone]] and [[Olga Yarynich]] and performed by [[Vasyl Lazarovych]], and was to represent [[Ukraine]] at the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2010]] in May 2010 in [[Oslo]], [[Norway]]. The song was selected on 6 March from five songs, all performed by Lazarovich.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurovision.tv/page/news?id=10093&_t=Ukraine%3A+Vasyl+Lazarovych+loves+you!|title=Ukraine: Vasyl Lazarovych loves you!|last=Omelyanchuk|first=Olena|date=2010-03-06|publisher=''[[European Broadcasting Union]]''|accessdate=6 March 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.esctoday.com/news/read/15313|title=Vasyl Lazarovich to perfom &#91;sic&#93; I love you in Eurovision|last=Klier|first=Marcus|date=2010-03-06|publisher=''ESCToday''|accessdate=6 March 2010}}</ref>
On 17 March 2010, it was announced by the [[National Television Company of Ukraine]] (NTU), the Ukrainian national broadcaster, that Vasyl Lazarovich's participation would be cancelled, and that a new national final would be held to select a new Ukrainian entry for the contest after complaints over the broadcaster's internal selection of Lazarovich and not letting other performers attempt to compete.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.esctoday.com/news/read/15402|title=Ukraine: National Final on March 20th|last=Murray|first=Gavin|date=2010-03-17|publisher=''ESCToday''|accessdate=17 March 2010}}</ref><ref name="New NF">{{cite web|url=http://www.eurovision.tv/page/news?id=10563&_t=Update%3A+The+list+of+participants+in+the+Ukrainian+final+released++|title=The list of participants in the Ukrainian final released |last=Omelyanchuk|first=Olena|date=2010-03-18|publisher=''[[European Broadcasting Union]]''|accessdate=18 March 2010}}</ref> Lazarovich later took part in the new national final with "I Love You" on 20 March to attempt to continue his Eurovision participation, however finished in 7th place.<ref name="New NF" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.esctoday.com/news/read/15407|title=Ukrainian 20 finalists selected|last=Hondal|first=Victor|date=2010-03-18|publisher=''ESCToday''|accessdate=18 March 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.esctoday.com/news/read/15413|title=Ukraine: 20 Finalists previewed|last=Montebello|first=Edward|date=2010-03-19|publisher=''ESCToday''|accessdate=19 March 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://1tv.com.ua/about/1tvnews/view.php?id=4180|title=20 National Final participants|publisher=''[[National Television Company of Ukraine|NTU]]''|language=Ukrainian|accessdate=19 March 2010}}</ref>
