{{Infobox newspaper | name = Literatura şi Arta | logo = | image = | caption = | type = | format = | owners = | founder = [[Victor Teleucă]] | publisher = | editor = | chiefeditor = [[Nicolae Dabija (politician)|Nicolae Dabija]] | assoceditor = | maneditor = | newseditor = | managingeditordesign = | campuseditor = | campuschief = | opeditor = | sportseditor = | photoeditor = | staff = | foundation = 1977 | political = | language = [[Romanian language|Romanian]] | ceased publication = | headquarters = [[Chişinău]] | circulation = | sister newspapers = | ISSN = | oclc = | website = [http://www.literaturasiarta.md/ Officialwebsite] }}
'''''Literatura şi Arta''''' ([[Romanian language|Romanian]] for "Literature and Art") is a weekly newspaper from [[Chişinău]], [[Moldova]].
== History ==
The first edition was printed in 1977. The first [[editor in chief]] was [[Victor Teleucă]] (1977–1983), Valeriu Senic (1983–1986). Among the authors were: , [[Dinu Mihail]], [[Mircea Blajinu]], [[Vlad Zbârciog]], [[Mihail Ion Cibotaru]], [[Iacob Burghiu]], [[Iulian Nicuţă]], [[Eugen Gheorghiţă]], [[Haralambie Moraru]], [[Ion Caţaveică]].
[[Nicolae Dabija (politician)|Nicolae Dabija]] has been the editor in chief of Literatura şi Arta since 1986.
