{{Infobox company | name = tivùsat | logo = Tivu-sat-logo.gif | type = Subsidiary of [[Tivù]] | foundation = 31 July 2009 | area_served = * Italy * Vatican City * Republic of San Marino | industry = [[Mass media|Media]] | services = FTA/FTV satellite television | owner = Joint venture between RAI, Mediaset and Telecom Italia Media | homepage = [http://www.tivu.tv/sat-eng/tivusat/index.aspx tivu.tv] }}
'''tivùsat''' is a [[free-to-air]]/[[free-to-view]] [[Digital television|digital]] [[satellite television]] platform, launched by the joint venture between [[RAI]], [[Mediaset]] and [[Telecom Italia|Telecom Italia Media]], and serving [[Italy]], [[Vatican City]] and [[San Marino]].
The service has been marketed since 31 July 2009 and offers a satellite alternative for many of those unable to receive the [[digital terrestrial television in Italy]]. Tivù Sat comprises free-to-air and free-to-view channels available on national television networks, and can be watched using a subscription card for Italian users purchasing a compatible receiver with [[Nagravision]] scrambling system.
